      "title": "Defining the clinical course of multiple sclerosis: the 2013 revisions",
      "abstract": "I read with interest the article by Lublin et al.1 When defining disease subtypes—like neuromyelitis optica—it is clear that pathophysiology should take precedence over clinical and subjective descriptions. The subtypes proposed by Lublin et al. are arbitrary and often diagnosed retrospectively. …"
